      "correctAnswerText": "1, 2, 3, 5",
      "explanation": "**Rationales:**\n\n✅ **Option 1 — Correct:** Smoking causes vasoconstriction that reduces oxygen delivery to tissues, impairs immune function, and slows healing.\n\n✅ **Option 2 — Correct:** Diabetes impairs wound healing through peripheral neuropathy, peripheral vascular disease, and hyperglycemia-induced leukocyte dysfunction.\n\n✅ **Option 3 — Correct:** Corticosteroids suppress the inflammatory phase of healing, inhibit fibroblast proliferation, and reduce collagen synthesis, all of which delay wound healing.\n\n❌ **Option 4 — Incorrect:** A protein intake of 1.25–1.5 g/kg/day is the recommended goal to *support* wound healing — it is beneficial, not harmful. This option would be an intervention to promote healing, not a risk factor for impairment.\n\n✅ **Option 5 — Correct:** Advanced age slows cell proliferation, reduces collagen synthesis, decreases immune response, and results in thinner, more fragile skin — all of which impair wound healing.\n\n---",
