      "explanation": "**Rationales:**\n\n❌ **A — Incorrect:** A Braden score of 19–23 indicates no risk. A score of 11 is in the high-risk range.\n\n❌ **B — Incorrect:** A Braden score of 15–18 indicates mild risk. Ambulation may be appropriate but is insufficient as the priority intervention for a high-risk patient.\n\n✅ **C — Correct:** A Braden score of 10–12 indicates high risk for pressure injury development. A comprehensive prevention protocol is required, including: repositioning every 2 hours, a pressure-redistributing support surface, moisture management, heel offloading, adequate nutrition and hydration, and frequent skin assessment.\n\n❌ **D — Incorrect:** A Braden score of 13–14 indicates moderate risk. A score of 11 requires more intensive intervention than moisturizer alone.\n\n---",
